Instructions to run ELK locally

##Elastic with Kibana and Logstash
>> docker run -d -p 9200:9200 -p 5601:5601 sebp/elk

##docker-compose.yml (must have docker-compose.yml at current branch)
>> docker-compose up elk 

To run locally:

For windows users:

>> sysctl -w vm.max_map_count=262144 (to solve some problems about memory crash)
>> wsl -d docker-desktop (must have Windows Subsystem for Linux)

http://localhost:9200/
http://localhost:5601/app/home#/
